The paper deals with game theory models for data injection attacks on smart grids, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.GT (Game Theory) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses security issues in the smart grid, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The use of models to study the interactions between the defender and attackers suggests that it could also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. The paper proposes a distributed learning algorithm, which could place it in the cs.CY (Control and Systems Engineering) sub-category. Finally, the use of algorithms to find equilibria in the game models suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
